description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STAFF NURSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ACUTE MEDICAL UNIT (AMU) &amp; SHORT STAY UNIT (SSU)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£24,907 - £30,615 per annum/pro rata (AfC Band 5)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;37.5 hours per week – PERMANENT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are a newly qualified staff nurse please apply via our Trust Wide advert where you will have the opportunity to specify your area of choice, please call 01226 431694 or 01226 432312 for further details.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for an exciting challenge with bespoke learning opportunities? Are you a highly motivated and dynamic individual? Then this could be the role for you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated nurses who are passionate about delivering high standards of care alongside a new senior leadership team who aim to lead the way in Acute Medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a positive attitude to the ever changing environment of Acute Medicine and Nursing and be willing to keep your knowledge and skills up to date&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AMU is a 45 bedded area that receives patients via ED and GP services who are undifferentiated and of high acuity, needing a high level of medical, physical and emotional support. AMU has an average turnover of 45 patients per day&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short Stay Unit is a 26 bedded area that offers an in- reach service to the Acute Medical Unit  (AMU) This is an invaluable service for the rapid assessment and discharge of patients. In a monthly period  there was an average turnover of 340 patients most of which were discharged within 24-48 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SSU is in the process of implementing an exciting new opportunity for  criteria led discharge&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both units have received excellence awards in recognition of their hard work and dedication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking enthusiastic, highly motivated individuals to be part of an innovative, multidisciplinary team involved in Acute Medicine. The successful candidate will possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills with a good understanding of admission and discharge processes to ensure effective patient flow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer posts on both AMU and SSU and rotational posts are available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is committed to promoting equality of opportunity and fair treatment to all applicants regardless of race, nationality, ethnic origin, gender, marital status, mental or physical disability, religion or belief, sexual orientation, age or offending history.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE: all correspondence regarding this vacancy and the interview process will be sent by e-mail.&lt;/strong&gt;  &lt;strong&gt;Therefore, you are advised to check your emails/NHS Jobs account regularly following the closing date.   To speed up the recruitment process please ensure that your references are appropriate and where possible you have provided an email address and telephone number.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding adults and children therefore if the post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (ROA) 1974 (Exceptions) Order 1975 (as amended) the successful candidate(s) will be subject to a criminal records check with the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS).  The cost of the DBS must be met by the successful candidate(s) through salary deduction. DBS charges for adverts placed from 1st June are as follows:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that these charges are not applicable for roles band 5 and below. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standard Check:    £23.00 + Administration cost of £3.69 = deduction from salary as a one off payment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enhanced Check:  £40.00 + administration cost of £3.69 = £13.69 deduction from 1st months’ salary, £10.00 deduction from salary over following 3 months.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date for applications: 8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview to be held on: TBC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please refer to the attached additional document when completing your application, this will inform you about Values Based Recruitment at Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
